GateDocument.TextWithNodes: Final Call for Papers International CAiSE'97 Workshop on Engineering Federated Database Systems ( EFDBS'97 ) Barcelona , Catalonia , 16 th and 17 th of June 1997 A federated database system ( FDBS ) is a loose integration of autonomous database systems , where both global applications accessing multiple database systems , and local applications are supported . The techniques for FDBS are employed in various application areas . The goal of the workshop is to bring together researchers interested in the development of FDBS . Workshop topics are : * CASE tool support for the development of FDBS * Software architectures for FDBS * Design and Implementation of FDBS * Influence of the application domain on the Design of FDBS * Evaluation of FDBS approaches The selection of presentations is on the basis of submitted extended abstracts ( about 2000 words ) which is done by the organizing committee : S . Conrad , Technical Information Systems , University of Magdeburg W . Hasselbring , Software Technology , University of Dortmund A . Heuer , Database Research Group , University of Rostock G . Saake , Technical Information Systems , University of Magdeburg Please send the PostScript files to willi @ mla . ws . nhj . The Proceedings will be available to the participants at the workshop which is celebrated in conjunction with the CAiSE'97 Conference . All workshop participants are expected to attend the main CAiSE'97 conference ( 16 - 20 June 1997 ) .
